Citation.sTitle: Influence of isoleucyl dipeptide side-chains on the dissociation and intermolecular interactions in water at 298.15K
Citation.sAbstract: Enthalpies of dissociation of four isoleucyl dipeptides having alkyl side-chains (l-isoleucine-glycine, l-Ile-Gly; l-isoleucine-l-alanine, l-Ilel- Ala; l-isoleucine-l-valine, l-Ile-l-Val; l-isoleucine-l-isoleucine, l-Ile-l-Ile) in water at 298.15K have been determined. Enthalpies of dilution have also been calculated. These results were used to derive the enthalpic coefficients of interactions according to the modified McMillan Mayer s model. The results are considered in an effort to establish a possible relation between dissociation, intermolecular interactions and the size of the alkyl side-chains.
